  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Executive / Senior Executive, Production Planning & Inventory Control",
  "description": "<p><strong>Primary Roles</strong></p><ul><li><p>Production plan for one or multiple products</p></li><li><p>Ensure an adequate and smooth supply of materials to support Production Plan</p></li><li><p>Responsible to meet customers’ requested delivery dates within reasonable lead-time for respective product lines.</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>Main Duties & Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Work with Sales admin on commitment of machines shipment to fulfil customers' required delivery date</p></li><li><p>Co-ordination of a successful MRP run following each plan release, focusing on respective product lines.</p></li><li><p>Plan material supply which correspondence to the production plan and agreed sales forecast</p></li><li><p>Ensure that respective product line has adequate material order quantity within stipulated lead time to fulfil production plan</p></li><li><p>Ensure that close follow-up with purchasing and suppliers in meeting material delivery dates thus maintaining smooth flow of materials to production.</p></li><li><p>Regular review of planning parameters to optimize inventory carriage and inventory turns for respective lines</p></li><li><p>Perform inventory analysis to maintain optimal stock level</p></li><li><p>Monitor and ensure all work/job orders are completed in timely manner</p></li><li><p>Co-ordination of engineering changes with minimum obsolescence and implementation of the engineering change to the production</p></li><li><p>Month end reporting of machines completion</p></li><li><p>Annual Year End Physical Inventory</p></li><li><p>Supervision of the respective team to ensure effective performance and achievement of objectives.</p></li><li><p>Lead digital transformation projects to enhance processes and productivity improvement</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Manufacturing/Production Engineering or a relevant discipline</p></li><li><p>Minimum 5 years of relevant working experience</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience with MRP systems (SAP) and the ability to understand system processes</p></li><li><p>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills</p></li><li><p>Management experience preferred</p></li><li><p>Demonstrated leadership skills and ability to motivate teams</p></li><li><p>Experience in the precision manufacturing industry is an advantage</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>Essential Attributes:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Resourceful and proactive</p></li><li><p>Strong and effective communication skills</p></li><li><p>Excellent organizational skills</p></li></ul>",
